I pay for the Pro version, and Otter has repeatedly failed me. While it works most of the time, it occasionally doesn't, and I don't know until after the recording is finished that it only transcribes a fraction of it. I'll record an 80-minute conversation, and then when I go back to look at the file, there'll be only 6 minutes. This is disastrous to my work as a news reporter.

Otter remains a convenient tool, but reliability has slipped. Recording from both phone and laptop has grown glitchier, and my latest 90-minute meeting has been ‚Äúprocessing‚Äù for six hours despite my paid plan. Transcription accuracy also trails other apps I use, leading to heavy edits‚Äîparticularly when multiple speakers have foreign accents. Useful, but increasingly frustrating.
